00:02:20.000 --> 00:02:22.000
IF YOU NOTICED IT.

00:02:22.000 --> 00:02:27.000
IT'S A SONG THAT GET
TO THE HEART OF MEN.

00:02:27.000 --> 00:02:41.000
* I ONCE WAS LOST
AND NOW I'M FOUND *

00:02:41.000 --> 00:02:56.000
* I WAS BLIND, BUT NOW I SEE. *

00:02:56.000 --> 00:02:59.000
Woman:
I THINK IT'S THE WORDS REALLY.

00:02:59.000 --> 00:03:01.000
A LOT OF THE TIME
THE MUSIC IS NICE

00:03:01.000 --> 00:03:05.000
BUT THE WORDS GET MORE
WITH THE PEOPLE THAN ANYTHING.

00:03:11.000 --> 00:03:14.000
( Judy Collins singing
 "Amazing Grace" )

00:03:14.000 --> 00:03:18.000
Collins:
I KNEW THIS SONG,
"AMAZING GRACE"

00:03:18.000 --> 00:03:23.000
FROM PROBABLY BEFORE I CAN
REMEMBER HAVING KNOWN IT.

00:03:23.000 --> 00:03:26.000
ONE DIDN'T THINK ABOUT HITS
IN THOSE DAYS

00:03:26.000 --> 00:03:29.000
EVEN THOUGH I'M SURE
THERE WERE PEOPLE

00:03:29.000 --> 00:03:31.000
WHO HAD TO THINK ABOUT
THAT SORT OF THING.

00:03:32.000 --> 00:03:35.000
I DIDN'T THINK OF IT
AS SOMETHING WITH MASS APPEAL.

00:03:35.000 --> 00:03:37.000
AND AS IT TURNED OUT

00:03:37.000 --> 00:03:40.000
THAT WAS THE SONG
THAT PEOPLE STARTED TO PLAY.

00:03:40.000 --> 00:03:42.000
IT WAS IN 1970, PEOPLE
STARTED TO REQUEST IT.

00:03:43.000 --> 00:03:46.000
DISC JOCKEYS STARTED TO PLAY IT,
BECOMING VERY, VERY POPULAR

00:03:46.000 --> 00:03:49.000
AND PEOPLE, I THINK,
TURNED TO IT

00:03:49.000 --> 00:03:51.000
AS THOUGH IT WAS SOMETHING

00:03:51.000 --> 00:03:53.000
THAT THEY'D ALREADY KNOWN

00:03:53.000 --> 00:03:56.000
AND AS THOUGH THEIR MEMORIES

00:03:56.000 --> 00:03:59.000
THEIR INNER MEMORY
WAS BEING REFRESHED

00:03:59.000 --> 00:04:01.000
SO THAT THEY KNEW IT.

00:04:01.000 --> 00:04:03.000
"AH, YES, I KNOW THAT."

00:04:03.000 --> 00:04:14.000
* AMAZING GRACE!
HOW SWEET THE SOUND *

00:04:14.000 --> 00:04:25.000
* THAT SAVED A WRETCH LIKE ME *

00:04:25.000 --> 00:04:36.000
* I ONCE WAS LOST,
BUT NOW I'M FOUND *

00:04:36.000 --> 00:04:46.000
* WAS BLIND BUT NOW I SEE. *

00:04:47.000 --> 00:04:51.000
( playing "Amazing Grace" )

00:05:00.000 --> 00:05:04.000
Ritchie:
I HAVE PEOPLE WHO SAY WHEN
I GET UP TO SING A FOLK SONG

00:05:04.000 --> 00:05:07.000
AN OLD SONG FROM THE FAMILY

00:05:07.000 --> 00:05:09.000
"THAT'S A QUAINT OLD THING.

00:05:09.000 --> 00:05:11.000
THESE THINGS ARE
REALLY ALL DEAD."

00:05:11.000 --> 00:05:14.000
I'D SAY THEY'RE NOT DEAD
OR THEY WOULDN'T BE HERE NOW.

00:05:14.000 --> 00:05:16.000
THEY'VE LIVED ALL THESE YEARS.

00:05:16.000 --> 00:05:19.000
THEY'VE GOT SOMETHING
TO OFFER TO PEOPLE

00:05:19.000 --> 00:05:21.000
AND SO HAVE OUR FAMILY MEMORIES.

00:05:27.000 --> 00:05:28.000
SEE THIS?

00:05:28.000 --> 00:05:30.000
I WONDER WHO
THAT IS?

00:05:30.000 --> 00:05:34.000
Man:
WE WERE ALL BOYS IN THE FAMILY
EXCEPT TEN.

00:05:34.000 --> 00:05:38.000
THERE WAS MAY, OLLIE, MATTIE,
UNA, RAYMOND, KITTY, TRUMAN

00:05:39.000 --> 00:05:42.000
PATTY, EDNA, JEWEL, PAULINE,
WILMER AND JEAN

00:05:42.000 --> 00:05:43.000
AND I'M WILBUR.

00:05:43.000 --> 00:05:46.000
THIS IS THE TENTH REUNION
THAT WE'VE HAD

00:05:46.000 --> 00:05:49.000
AND WE'RE VERY FORTUNATE

00:05:49.000 --> 00:05:51.000
THERE ARE SO MANY LEFT

00:05:51.000 --> 00:05:54.000
THAT WE CAN SEE
ALL THESE GRANDCHILDREN.

00:05:54.000 --> 00:05:59.000
Group:
* THE SUN REFUSED TO SHINE *

00:05:59.000 --> 00:06:02.000
Woman:
THE LORD WHO SENT ME HERE BELOW.

00:06:02.000 --> 00:06:06.000
Group:
* THE LORD WHO SENT ME... *

00:06:06.000 --> 00:06:09.000
Wilbur:
WE USED TO SET ON THE FRONT
PORCH OF THIS OLD HOUSE

00:06:09.000 --> 00:06:11.000
BEFORE IT WAS REMODELED.

00:06:11.000 --> 00:06:13.000
WE HAD A SWING OUT THERE.

00:06:13.000 --> 00:06:16.000
IN THE EVENINGS,
THEY WOULD SET AND SING

00:06:16.000 --> 00:06:20.000
AND USUALLY THAT
WAS THE LAST SONG

00:06:20.000 --> 00:06:24.000
THAT THEY SUNG--
"AMAZING GRACE."

00:06:24.000 --> 00:06:27.000
MY MOTHER SANG IT, I REMEMBER
EVEN MY FATHER SINGING.

00:06:27.000 --> 00:06:31.000
MY MOTHER BELONGED TO THE
OLD REGULAR BAPTIST CHURCH

00:06:31.000 --> 00:06:32.000
AT JEFF, KENTUCKY

00:06:32.000 --> 00:06:35.000
AND I REMEMBER WHEN
I WAS A LITTLE BOY

00:06:35.000 --> 00:06:38.000
I WOULD GO WITH HER DOWN THERE

00:06:38.000 --> 00:06:40.000
AND THEY WOULD
LINE OFF THE SONGS

00:06:40.000 --> 00:06:44.000
AND I CAN REMEMBER SO WELL
THE PREACHER WOULD GET UP THERE

00:06:44.000 --> 00:06:48.000
AND HE'D SAY, "AMAZING GRACE,
HOW SWEET ITS SOUND."

00:06:48.000 --> 00:06:50.000
AND EVERYBODY WOULD SING

00:06:50.000 --> 00:06:53.000
* AMAZING GRACE!
HOW SWEET THE SOUND *

00:06:53.000 --> 00:06:55.000
"THAT SAVED A WRETCH LIKE ME."

00:06:55.000 --> 00:07:00.000
AND THEN THEY'D ALL COME OUT,
* THAT SAVED A WRETCH LIKE ME. *

00:07:00.000 --> 00:07:03.000
"ONCE I WAS LOST
BUT NOW I'M FOUND," AND SO ON.

00:07:03.000 --> 00:07:07.000
IT WENT ON THROUGH THE WHOLE
THING LIKE THAT.

00:07:07.000 --> 00:07:09.000
IT WAS REALLY TOUCHING
FOR A YOUNG BOY.

00:07:09.000 --> 00:07:12.000
IT MADE THE SHIVERS
RUN OVER YOU.

00:07:12.000 --> 00:07:15.000
WE SANG IT EVERY TIME
WE WOULD SING HYMNS.

00:07:15.000 --> 00:07:17.000
IN FACT, I REMEMBER AS A CHILD

00:07:17.000 --> 00:07:20.000
MY COUSIN AND I TALKED
ABOUT THIS ONE TIME.

00:07:20.000 --> 00:07:23.000
SHE TOLD ME,
"I USED TO HIDE IN THE CLOSET

00:07:23.000 --> 00:07:26.000
WHEN THEY SANG THE HYMNS
BECAUSE I'D BE CRYING SO HARD."

00:07:27.000 --> 00:07:28.000
I DO THE SAME THING.

00:07:28.000 --> 00:07:31.000
EVERY TIME THEY START
SINGING THESE HYMNS

00:07:31.000 --> 00:07:34.000
TEARS JUST START
COMING OUT OF MY EYES

00:07:34.000 --> 00:07:35.000
AND I DON'T KNOW WHY.

00:07:35.000 --> 00:07:37.000
IT JUST REALLY
AFFECTS ME SOME WAY.

00:07:38.000 --> 00:07:42.000
IT'S LIKE ROOTS
JUST REACHING SO FAR DOWN.

00:07:43.000 --> 00:07:46.000
* ...LIKE ME *

00:07:47.000 --> 00:07:52.000
* I ONCE WAS LOST *

00:07:52.000 --> 00:07:57.000
* BUT NOW I'M FOUND *

00:07:57.000 --> 00:08:10.000
* WAS BLIND BUT NOW I SEE. *

00:08:10.000 --> 00:08:16.000
THE RITCHIES CAME OVER TO THIS
COUNTRY FROM SCOTLAND IN 1768.

00:08:16.000 --> 00:08:20.000
I IMAGINE THIS SONG...
WAS IT WRITTEN AFTER THAT?

00:08:20.000 --> 00:08:22.000
Moyers:
IT WAS WRITTEN
ABOUT THAT TIME.

00:08:23.000 --> 00:08:24.000
YOU KNOW
WHO WROTE IT?

00:08:24.000 --> 00:08:25.000
ISAAC NEWTON.

00:08:25.000 --> 00:08:27.000
JOHN NEWTON.

00:08:27.000 --> 00:08:28.000
I KNEW IT WAS A NEWTON.

00:08:29.000 --> 00:08:30.000
KNOW ANYTHING
ABOUT HIM?

00:08:30.000 --> 00:08:32.000
NO, I JUST SEEN
HIS NAME ON THE SONG.

00:08:32.000 --> 00:08:38.000
( organ playing
 "Amazing Grace" )

00:08:45.000 --> 00:08:53.000
Choir:
* AMAZING GRACE
HOW SWEET THE SOUND *

00:08:53.000 --> 00:09:01.000
* THAT SAVED A WRETCH LIKE ME *

00:09:02.000 --> 00:09:11.000
* I ONCE WAS LOST
BUT NOW I'M FOUND *

00:09:11.000 --> 00:09:13.000
* WAS BLIND... *

00:09:13.000 --> 00:09:18.000
Man:
JOHN NEWTON WAS IN HIS OWN WORDS
"AN INFIDEL AND A LIBERTINE"

00:09:18.000 --> 00:09:20.000
IN THE EARLY PART OF HIS LIFE

00:09:20.000 --> 00:09:23.000
BUT LATER ON HE WAS
A REFORMED CHARACTER

00:09:23.000 --> 00:09:27.000
AND BECAME A CHRISTIAN MINISTER
IN THE CHURCH OF ENGLAND.

00:09:27.000 --> 00:09:28.000
HE WAS BORN IN 1725

00:09:28.000 --> 00:09:31.000
AND HE DIED IN 1807,
SO HE HAD A GOOD LIFE.

00:09:31.000 --> 00:09:33.000
THE EARLY PART
OF HIS LIFE, THOUGH

00:09:33.000 --> 00:09:36.000
WAS CLOUDED WITH
SHAME AND DISGRACE

00:09:36.000 --> 00:09:38.000
ACCORDING TO HIS LATER THOUGHTS.

00:09:38.000 --> 00:09:40.000
BUT HE WROTE THE HYMN
"AMAZING GRACE"

00:09:40.000 --> 00:09:42.000
WHEN HE TOOK HIS FIRST CURE

00:09:42.000 --> 00:09:46.000
IN THE PARISH OF OLNEY IN
THE COUNTY OF BUCKINGHAMSHIRE.

00:09:46.000 --> 00:09:50.000
HE PROBABLY WROTE IT IN
THE YEARS ABOUT 1760 TO 1770.

00:09:50.000 --> 00:09:53.000
Man:
JOHN NEWTON WAS THE CURATE
HERE IN OLNEY.

00:09:53.000 --> 00:09:55.000
HE WAS APPOINTED IN 1764

00:09:56.000 --> 00:09:59.000
AND STARTED A VERY LIVELY
SORT OF PREACHING

00:09:59.000 --> 00:10:02.000
ABOUT HIMSELF
AND HIS OWN EXPERIENCE

00:10:02.000 --> 00:10:04.000
AND THE WORK OF GRACE
IN HIS LIFE.

00:10:04.000 --> 00:10:06.000
IN ADDITION TO
THE CHURCH SERVICES

00:10:06.000 --> 00:10:08.000
HE STARTED A WEEKLY
PRAYER MEETING.

00:10:09.000 --> 00:10:11.000
AND HE PERSUADED
HIS FRIEND WILLIAM COWPER

00:10:12.000 --> 00:10:14.000
WHO LATER BECAME
QUITE FAMOUS AS A POET

00:10:14.000 --> 00:10:17.000
TO WRITE HYMNS TOGETHER WITH HIM

00:10:17.000 --> 00:10:20.000
SO THEY WOULD TAKE TURNS
TO WRITE A NEW HYMN

00:10:20.000 --> 00:10:22.000
FOR EACH OF THESE
WEEKLY MEETINGS.

00:10:22.000 --> 00:10:25.000
"AMAZING GRACE"
WAS ONE OF THOSE.

00:10:25.000 --> 00:10:26.000
AS FAR AS WE KNOW

00:10:26.000 --> 00:10:30.000
IT WAS WRITTEN IN HIS STUDY
RIGHT AT THE TOP THERE

00:10:30.000 --> 00:10:33.000
THE TOP RIGHT-HAND ROOM
OF THE VICARAGE.

00:10:33.000 --> 00:10:38.000
John Newton:
 OCTOBER 27, 1778.

00:10:38.000 --> 00:10:41.000
HOW INDUSTRIOUSLY
 IS SATAN SERVED.

00:10:41.000 --> 00:10:46.000
I WAS FORMERLY ONE
 OF HIS ACTIVE UNDERTEMPTERS

00:10:46.000 --> 00:10:50.000
AND HAD MY INFLUENCE
 BEEN EQUAL TO MY WISHES

00:10:50.000 --> 00:10:54.000
I WOULD HAVE CARRIED
 ALL THE HUMAN RACE WITH ME.

00:10:54.000 --> 00:10:57.000
A COMMON DRUNKARD
 OR PROFLIGATE

00:10:57.000 --> 00:11:00.000
IS A PETTY SINNER
 TO WHAT I WAS.

00:11:00.000 --> 00:11:04.000
I HAD THE AMBITION OF A CAESAR
 OR AN ALEXANDER

00:11:04.000 --> 00:11:07.000
AND WANTED TO RANK
 IN WICKEDNESS

00:11:07.000 --> 00:11:10.000
AMONG THE FOREMOST
 OF THE HUMAN RACE.

00:11:11.000 --> 00:11:14.000
OH, TO GRACE,
 HOW GREAT A DEBTOR.

00:11:14.000 --> 00:11:16.000
"THOU SHALT REMEMBER

00:11:16.000 --> 00:11:20.000
"THAT THOU WAST A BOND-MAN
 IN THE LAND OF EGYPT

00:11:20.000 --> 00:11:24.000
AND THE LORD THY GOD
 REDEEMED THEE."

00:11:24.000 --> 00:11:27.000
NEWTON'S BACKGROUND WAS
PRETTY ROUGH, REALLY.

00:11:27.000 --> 00:11:29.000
HE CAME FROM A SEAFARING FAMILY.

00:11:29.000 --> 00:11:31.000
HE LOST HIS MOTHER
AT AN EARLY AGE.

00:11:31.000 --> 00:11:34.000
HE DIDN'T DO MUCH
AT SCHOOL AT ALL

00:11:34.000 --> 00:11:38.000
BUT HIS FATHER EVENTUALLY
MANAGED TO GET HIM A JOB AT SEA

00:11:38.000 --> 00:11:39.000
BUT HE RAN AWAY

00:11:39.000 --> 00:11:42.000
AND THEN HE GOT PRESS-GANGED
INTO THE NAVY

00:11:42.000 --> 00:11:44.000
AND THEN HE MUTINIED
FROM ANOTHER SHIP--

00:11:44.000 --> 00:11:46.000
HE HAD A VERY ROUGH TIME--

00:11:46.000 --> 00:11:49.000
AND THEN HE ENDED UP
IN THE SLAVE TRADE.

00:11:49.000 --> 00:11:51.000
Cooke:
ONE OF HIS MAIN EXPERIENCES

00:11:51.000 --> 00:11:54.000
WHEN HE WAS GIVEN THE COMMAND
OF A SHIP OUT OF LIVERPOOL

00:11:55.000 --> 00:11:57.000
WAS TO TAKE MANUFACTURED ITEMS
FROM GREAT BRITAIN

00:11:57.000 --> 00:11:59.000
AND EXPORT THEM TO WEST AFRICA

00:11:59.000 --> 00:12:04.000
AND THERE HE WOULD EXCHANGE THEM
WITH THE TRADERS ON THE COAST

00:12:04.000 --> 00:12:06.000
FOR SLAVES.

00:12:06.000 --> 00:12:08.000
MONDAY NOVEMBER 12, 1750.

00:12:08.000 --> 00:12:12.000
THIS MORNING MR. CLOUGH
 SHOWED ME SEVEN SLAVES

00:12:12.000 --> 00:12:16.000
OUT OF WHICH I PICKED FOUR,
 THREE MEN, ONE WOMAN

00:12:16.000 --> 00:12:20.000
PAID WHAT GOODS I HAD
 IN THE BOAT THAT WERE SUITABLE

00:12:20.000 --> 00:12:22.000
AND I'M TO SEND THE REST.

00:12:22.000 --> 00:12:26.000
IN THE AFTERNOON,
 WEIGHED WITH THE SEA BREEZE

00:12:26.000 --> 00:12:31.000
AND RAN HALFWAY TO THE BANANAS,
 THEN IT FELL CALM.

00:12:31.000 --> 00:12:32.000
HE WAS A PROLIFIC WRITER

00:12:32.000 --> 00:12:35.000
AND THAT'S MADE
ALL THE DIFFERENCE

00:12:35.000 --> 00:12:36.000
TO OUR KNOWLEDGE OF HIM.

00:12:37.000 --> 00:12:39.000
HE KEPT NOT ONLY A DAILY JOURNAL

00:12:39.000 --> 00:12:41.000
WHICH HE WROTE EXTENSIVELY

00:12:41.000 --> 00:12:43.000
BUT ALSO HIS WHOLE
VOLUME OF LETTERS

00:12:43.000 --> 00:12:46.000
AND HISTORIANS TELL ME

00:12:46.000 --> 00:12:49.000
THAT JOHN NEWTON'S
JOURNAL AND LETTERS

00:12:49.000 --> 00:12:52.000
WERE THE FIRST REALLY
IMPORTANT ACCOUNT

00:12:52.000 --> 00:12:57.000
OF WHAT IT WAS LIKE TO BE AT SEA
IN THE SLAVE TRADE BUSINESS.

00:12:57.000 --> 00:13:01.000
MONDAY JANUARY 7, 1751.

00:13:01.000 --> 00:13:03.000
THIS MORNING, WENT ON BOARD
 CAPTAIN COBURN

00:13:03.000 --> 00:13:06.000
HE HAVING TOLD ME
 HE HAD EIGHT SLAVES

00:13:06.000 --> 00:13:08.000
TO CHANGE WITH ME
 FOR TEETH AND WOOD

00:13:08.000 --> 00:13:11.000
ACCORDING TO OUR AGREEMENT
 OF THE BANANAS

00:13:11.000 --> 00:13:14.000
BUT COULD NOT TAKE THEM
 UPON HIS TERMS

00:13:14.000 --> 00:13:16.000
WHICH WAS 60 BARS
 PER HEAD ROUND

00:13:16.000 --> 00:13:18.000
THOUGH THERE WERE
 BUT THREE SIZEABLE

00:13:18.000 --> 00:13:22.000
AND TWO OF THE REMAINING FIVE
 UNDER THREE FOOT, SIX INCHES.

00:13:22.000 --> 00:13:24.000
SENT THE STEWARD
 TO SHORE AGAIN

00:13:25.000 --> 00:13:27.000
TO PURCHASE THE WOMAN SLAVE

00:13:27.000 --> 00:13:30.000
AND BROUGHT HER OFF
 IN THE EVENING, NUMBER 46.

00:13:30.000 --> 00:13:35.000
SHE COST 63 BARS, THOUGH SHE
 HAD A VERY BAD MOUTH.

00:13:35.000 --> 00:13:39.000
Cooke:
HE OF COURSE HAD A FINANCIAL
INTEREST IN THE VOYAGE.

00:13:39.000 --> 00:13:42.000
IF THE TRIP WAS SUCCESSFUL
AND HE MADE MONEY

00:13:42.000 --> 00:13:44.000
THEN HE COULD TAKE
A SHARE OF IT.

00:13:44.000 --> 00:13:47.000
THIS WAS PARTICULARLY
IMPORTANT TO HIM

00:13:47.000 --> 00:13:49.000
BECAUSE HIS SWEETHEART'S PARENTS

00:13:49.000 --> 00:13:53.000
WERE KEEN THAT HE BE
ESTABLISHED IN LIFE WITH MONEY

00:13:53.000 --> 00:13:55.000
IN ORDER TO MARRY
THEIR ELDEST DAUGHTER

00:13:55.000 --> 00:13:59.000
AND WITHOUT THAT MONEY
HE WAS DOOMED TO FAILURE.

00:13:59.000 --> 00:14:03.000
USUALLY ABOUT TWO-THIRDS
 OF A CARGO OF SLAVES ARE MALES.

00:14:03.000 --> 00:14:07.000
WHEN 150 OR 200 STOUT MEN
 TORN FROM THEIR NATIVE LAND

00:14:07.000 --> 00:14:10.000
AND WHO OFTEN BRING
 WITH THEM AN APPREHENSION

00:14:10.000 --> 00:14:12.000
THEY ARE BOUGHT TO BE EATEN

00:14:12.000 --> 00:14:16.000
WHEN THUS CIRCUMSTANCED,
 IT IS NOT TO BE EXPECTED

00:14:16.000 --> 00:14:20.000
THAT THEY WILL TAMELY RESIGN
 THEMSELVES TO THEIR SITUATION.

00:14:20.000 --> 00:14:22.000
IT IS ALWAYS TAKEN FOR GRANTED

00:14:22.000 --> 00:14:25.000
THAT THEY WILL ATTEMPT
 TO GAIN THEIR LIBERTY.

00:14:25.000 --> 00:14:29.000
ACCORDINGLY, AS WE DARE
 NOT TRUST THEM

00:14:29.000 --> 00:14:33.000
WE RECEIVE THEM ON BOARD
 FROM THE FIRST AS ENEMIES.

00:14:34.000 --> 00:14:37.000
Burdon:
HE SAW HIMSELF VERY MUCH
AS A FREE THINKER

00:14:37.000 --> 00:14:40.000
WHO WAS NOTORIOUS AMONG
THE SAILORS APPARENTLY--

00:14:40.000 --> 00:14:42.000
WHO WERE A FAIRLY
ROUGH LOT THEN--

00:14:42.000 --> 00:14:45.000
FOR THE TERRIBLE OATHS
THAT HE USED

00:14:45.000 --> 00:14:47.000
AND THIS QUITE ALARMED THEM.

00:14:47.000 --> 00:14:50.000
ONE DAY HE WAS IN THE ATLANTIC
IN A STORM AT SEA

00:14:50.000 --> 00:14:53.000
AND IT SEEMED AS THOUGH
THE SHIP WAS SINKING

00:14:53.000 --> 00:14:55.000
AND EVERYTHING WOULD BE LOST

00:14:55.000 --> 00:14:58.000
AND HE SUDDENLY EXCLAIMED,
"WELL, IF NOTHING CAN BE DONE

00:14:58.000 --> 00:15:00.000
LORD HAVE MERCY UPON US."

00:15:00.000 --> 00:15:04.000
HE WENT BACK TO HIS CABIN AND
THOUGHT ABOUT WHAT HE HAD SAID

00:15:04.000 --> 00:15:07.000
AND WHAT DID THIS MEAN,
"LORD HAVE MERCY UPON US"?

00:15:07.000 --> 00:15:11.000
THIS WASN'T THE SORT OF THING
HE WAS SUPPOSED TO BELIEVE IN.

00:15:11.000 --> 00:15:15.000
SOMEHOW HE REALIZED THAT THERE
IN THE MIDDLE OF THE STORM

00:15:15.000 --> 00:15:18.000
GOD HAD ADDRESSED HIM,
THAT HE BELIEVED IN GOD

00:15:18.000 --> 00:15:22.000
AND GOD'S GRACE WAS WORKING
ACTUALLY IN HIM AND FOR HIM

00:15:22.000 --> 00:15:24.000
AND GRADUALLY HIS LIFE CHANGED.

00:15:24.000 --> 00:15:37.000
