00:16:04.000 --> 00:16:23.000
* I ONCE WAS LOST,
BUT NOW I'M FOUND *

00:16:24.000 --> 00:16:41.000
* WAS BLIND, BUT NOW I SEE. *

00:16:41.000 --> 00:16:59.000
* 'TWAS GRACE THAT TAUGHT
MY HEART TO FEAR *

00:16:59.000 --> 00:17:17.000
* AND GRACE MY FEARS RELIEVED *

00:17:17.000 --> 00:17:35.000
* HOW PRECIOUS DID
THAT GRACE APPEAR *

00:17:35.000 --> 00:17:48.000
* THE HOUR I FIRST BELIEVED. *

00:17:48.000 --> 00:17:52.000
Norman:
THE FIRST TIME I HEARD IT
MUST HAVE BEEN IN CHURCH.

00:17:52.000 --> 00:17:55.000
THIS WAS WHAT CHURCH
MEANT TO ME-- THE MUSIC.

00:17:55.000 --> 00:17:58.000
AND I'M SURE THAT IT
WAS DONE A CAPPELLA

00:17:58.000 --> 00:18:00.000
AND IT WAS PROBABLY
DONE IN THE WAY

00:18:00.000 --> 00:18:03.000
THAT WE REFER TO
IN THE BAPTIST CHURCH

00:18:03.000 --> 00:18:05.000
THAT THE HYMN WAS "RAISED"

00:18:05.000 --> 00:18:06.000
THAT SOME DEACON STOOD UP

00:18:07.000 --> 00:18:08.000
JUST AS THEY WOULD

00:18:08.000 --> 00:18:09.000
IN AN AFRICAN TRIBE

00:18:09.000 --> 00:18:12.000
AND SAID, "I WANT TO SING
'AMAZING GRACE'

00:18:12.000 --> 00:18:14.000
A HYMN IN COMMON METER."

00:18:14.000 --> 00:18:15.000
AND HE STARTS TO SING

00:18:15.000 --> 00:18:17.000
AND THEN THE CHURCH
JOINS IN.

00:18:17.000 --> 00:18:20.000
DOES IT SURPRISE YOU
THAT THIS SONG

00:18:20.000 --> 00:18:24.000
HAS NOW BECOME SO
UNIVERSALLY POPULAR?

00:18:25.000 --> 00:18:25.000
YES.

00:18:26.000 --> 00:18:28.000
AND RECOGNIZED AND RECEIVED?

00:18:28.000 --> 00:18:29.000
YES, I AM
SURPRISED
BY THAT

00:18:30.000 --> 00:18:32.000
AND I WAS SURPRISED
AT THE POPULARITY

00:18:32.000 --> 00:18:35.000
THAT THE SONG SEEMED
TO GAIN IN THE '60s.

00:18:35.000 --> 00:18:38.000
I WAS VERY SURPRISED BY THAT.

00:18:38.000 --> 00:18:42.000
UNTIL THEN IT WAS
PRETTY WELL IN THE PROVINCE

00:18:42.000 --> 00:18:43.000
OF RELIGIOUS FOLKS.

00:18:43.000 --> 00:18:46.000
SOMEHOW THE GENIE GOT
OUT OF THE BOTTLE.

00:18:46.000 --> 00:18:48.000
YEAH, IT REALLY DID,
AND IT STAYED THERE.

00:18:48.000 --> 00:18:54.000
Collins:
FOR ME, IT WAS ALWAYS
THE SONG THAT GAVE ME

00:18:54.000 --> 00:18:57.000
AN INNER EXPERIENCE
OF AN OTHER DIMENSION.

00:18:57.000 --> 00:19:00.000
WHEN I SING THIS SONG
WITH A GROUP OF PEOPLE

00:19:00.000 --> 00:19:03.000
I ALWAYS FEEL THAT
THERE'S A MYSTICAL TERRITORY

00:19:03.000 --> 00:19:06.000
BETWEEN THE SINGER
AND THE AUDIENCE.

00:19:06.000 --> 00:19:08.000
IT'S NOT JUST ME SINGING

00:19:08.000 --> 00:19:10.000
IT'S SOMETHING ELSE
THAT'S SINGING

00:19:10.000 --> 00:19:13.000
AND IT'S ALL OF THOSE PEOPLE
AND THEIR SPIRITS

00:19:13.000 --> 00:19:17.000
SO SOMEWHERE OR OTHER THERE IS
SOME EXPERIENCE GOING ON

00:19:17.000 --> 00:19:20.000
WHICH GIVES SOMETHING TO THEM
AND GIVES SOMETHING TO ME

00:19:20.000 --> 00:19:24.000
THAT'S MORE THAN THE SUM
OF ANY OF US.

00:19:24.000 --> 00:19:32.000
* ...HOW SWEET THE SOUND *
THAT SAVED THE...

00:19:32.000 --> 00:19:35.000
I HAD HEARD THAT THE SONG
WAS WRITTEN BY A MAN

00:19:35.000 --> 00:19:39.000
WHO HAD HAD A WRETCHED LIFE
AND BEEN A SLAVE TRADER.

00:19:39.000 --> 00:19:44.000
WHAT AN EXPRESSION OF...
YES, OF GRATITUDE AND OF JOY

00:19:44.000 --> 00:19:48.000
TO KNOW THAT THERE WAS...
IS THE OTHER SIDE TO THAT

00:19:48.000 --> 00:19:52.000
WHICH CAN ONLY BE GIVEN
BY SUCH A PROFOUND

00:19:52.000 --> 00:19:55.000
AND I WOULD CALL
SPIRITUAL EXPERIENCE.

00:19:56.000 --> 00:20:00.000
"AMAZING GRACE" REALLY SAYS
THIS CHOICE IS WRETCHED

00:20:00.000 --> 00:20:02.000
AND THIS OTHER ONE
IS WORLDS APART.

00:20:02.000 --> 00:20:04.000
INDESCRIBABLE.

00:20:04.000 --> 00:20:06.000
DID YOU EVER FEEL
LIKE A WRETCH?

00:20:06.000 --> 00:20:09.000
OH, YES, ENOUGH SO
THAT IT ALWAYS REMINDS ME

00:20:10.000 --> 00:20:14.000
THAT THERE HAVE BEEN THOSE VERY,
VERY DARK TIMES IN MY OWN LIFE

00:20:15.000 --> 00:20:19.000
SOME OF WHICH, DURING SOME
OF WHICH, THIS SONG I THINK

00:20:19.000 --> 00:20:21.000
REALLY CARRIED ME THROUGH.

00:20:21.000 --> 00:20:24.000
"AMAZING GRACE" IS ALMOST
LIKE A TALISMAN.

00:20:24.000 --> 00:20:28.000
WHAT WERE SOME OF THE DEEPEST
OR DARKEST DANGERS

00:20:28.000 --> 00:20:30.000
THAT YOU EXPERIENCED

00:20:30.000 --> 00:20:33.000
WHEN THIS
ILLUMINATION
WAS IMPORTANT?

00:20:34.000 --> 00:20:38.000
I THINK IT WAS ALCOHOL
PERHAPS MOST OF ALL

00:20:38.000 --> 00:20:42.000
BECAUSE DURING THOSE TIMES
PARTICULARLY

00:20:42.000 --> 00:20:45.000
I THINK THAT SONG WAS THE THING

00:20:45.000 --> 00:20:47.000
THAT WAS ABLE
TO PULL ME THROUGH.

00:20:47.000 --> 00:20:49.000
IT HEALS.

00:20:49.000 --> 00:21:01.000
* ...BUT NOW I SEE. *

00:21:01.000 --> 00:21:02.000
BEAUTIFUL.

00:21:08.000 --> 00:21:12.000
I REMEMBER BEING IN MISSISSIPPI
WITH FANNIE LOU HAMER

00:21:12.000 --> 00:21:16.000
AND GOING ON THE VOTER
REGISTRATION DRIVES

00:21:16.000 --> 00:21:17.000
IN THE SUMMER OF '64

00:21:17.000 --> 00:21:19.000
AND WE'D GET TO THE TOWN

00:21:19.000 --> 00:21:23.000
WHERE WE WERE TO DO A RALLY
FOR VOTER REGISTRATION

00:21:23.000 --> 00:21:26.000
DREW, MISSISSIPPI
OR RULEVILLE, MISSISSIPPI

00:21:26.000 --> 00:21:27.000
LITTLE TINY TOWNS

00:21:27.000 --> 00:21:32.000
WHERE PEOPLE WERE REALLY
RISKING THEIR LIVES TO COME OUT

00:21:32.000 --> 00:21:34.000
AND THEY WOULD COME.

00:21:34.000 --> 00:21:38.000
THE THING THAT BROUGHT THEM OUT
WAS THE SINGING.

00:21:39.000 --> 00:21:41.000
FANNIE LOU HAMER
WAS A GREAT SINGER

00:21:41.000 --> 00:21:43.000
AND WHEN SHE WOULD SING
"AMAZING GRACE"

00:21:43.000 --> 00:21:45.000
YOU COULDN'T HELP BUT SING

00:21:45.000 --> 00:21:48.000
AND YOU COULDN'T HELP
BUT FEEL MOVED

00:21:48.000 --> 00:21:51.000
AND YOU COULD EVEN SEE
THAT THE PEOPLE WHO WERE THERE

00:21:51.000 --> 00:21:53.000
TO PERHAPS PREVENT
WHAT WAS GOING ON

00:21:54.000 --> 00:21:55.000
EVEN THEY WERE INVOLVED.

00:21:55.000 --> 00:21:56.000
YOU CAN'T HELP IT.

00:21:56.000 --> 00:22:00.000
IT'S TERRIBLY IMPORTANT
TO HEAR YOUR OWN HEART

00:22:00.000 --> 00:22:03.000
REFLECT THE HEARTS
OF OTHER PEOPLE

00:22:03.000 --> 00:22:07.000
AND THE SONG I THINK FITS
ALMOST EVERY SITUATION

00:22:07.000 --> 00:22:08.000
YOU WOULD PUT IT IN.

00:22:08.000 --> 00:22:16.000
Marchers:
* BUT NOW I SEE. *

00:22:16.000 --> 00:22:18.000
Norman:
I DIDN'T KNOW THAT THE MELODY

00:22:18.000 --> 00:22:21.000
THAT WE KNOW IS AN
AMERICAN FOLK MELODY.

00:22:21.000 --> 00:22:23.000
WE DON'T KNOW
HOW THIS CAME TO BE.

00:22:23.000 --> 00:22:27.000
BUT IT'S INTERESTING--
THE LIFE OF JOHN NEWTON.

00:22:27.000 --> 00:22:31.000
I FIND THIS QUITE UNBELIEVABLE,
THAT HE'D BEEN ABOARD SHIPS

00:22:31.000 --> 00:22:33.000
WHERE SLAVES WERE TRANSPORTED

00:22:33.000 --> 00:22:36.000
FROM WEST AFRICA TO ENGLAND
OR TO THE UNITED STATES

00:22:36.000 --> 00:22:39.000
AND THAT HE FOUND GRACE
AND CHANGED HIS WAYS.

00:22:40.000 --> 00:22:41.000
I MEAN, THIS IS AMAZING.

00:22:41.000 --> 00:22:44.000
THE THING THAT I WAS
THINKING ABOUT

00:22:44.000 --> 00:22:46.000
READING THE MATERIAL

00:22:46.000 --> 00:22:49.000
IS THAT WOULDN'T IT BE
QUITE UNBELIEVABLE

00:22:49.000 --> 00:22:53.000
IF THIS MELODY WERE
ORIGINALLY A SLAVE MELODY

00:22:53.000 --> 00:22:56.000
AND THESE WORDS WERE
WRITTEN BY JOHN NEWTON?

00:22:56.000 --> 00:22:59.000
WOULDN'T THAT BE AN
INCREDIBLE COINCIDENCE?

00:22:59.000 --> 00:23:02.000
YOU'VE SUNG IT IN MANY PLACES.

00:23:02.000 --> 00:23:04.000
I'VE SUNG IT WITH ORCHESTRA.

00:23:04.000 --> 00:23:08.000
LAST SUMMER I SANG IT QUITE
A LOT AT THE END OF RECITALS.

00:23:08.000 --> 00:23:10.000
THERE WAS A WONDERFUL CONCERT

00:23:11.000 --> 00:23:12.000
IT WAS REALLY A ROCK CONCERT

00:23:12.000 --> 00:23:14.000
FOR THE 70th BIRTHDAY
OF NELSON MANDELA

00:23:14.000 --> 00:23:17.000
IN LONDON LAST JUNE

00:23:17.000 --> 00:23:19.000
AND AT THE END OF THIS CONCERT

00:23:19.000 --> 00:23:21.000
WHICH WENT ON FOR HOURS--

00:23:21.000 --> 00:23:24.000
I THINK IT MUST HAVE BEEN
12 HOURS OF ROCK MUSIC--

00:23:24.000 --> 00:23:27.000
THERE I WAS STANDING
IN A WHITE SPOTLIGHT AT THE END

00:23:27.000 --> 00:23:29.000
WITH 70,000 ROCK FANS

00:23:29.000 --> 00:23:33.000
THAT REALLY WANTED THE DIRE
STRAITS TO GO ON ONE MORE SONG

00:23:33.000 --> 00:23:36.000
AND OUT I CAME TO SING
"AMAZING GRACE."

00:23:36.000 --> 00:23:38.000
Moyers:
WAS THAT SPONTANEOUS?

00:23:38.000 --> 00:23:41.000
Norman:
NO, I WAS ASKED TO DO IT.

00:23:41.000 --> 00:23:43.000
I WASN'T SURE THAT
WAS A GOOD IDEA

00:23:43.000 --> 00:23:47.000
AND A LOT OF THE ROCK FANS
DID NOT UNDERSTAND.

00:23:47.000 --> 00:23:51.000
BUT AFTER A WHILE THEY FINALLY
QUIETED DOWN TO LISTEN

00:23:51.000 --> 00:23:53.000
AND SOME OF THEM SANG WITH ME

00:23:53.000 --> 00:23:56.000
AND THOUGHT THAT THEY WERE
FORCED TO REMEMBER

00:23:56.000 --> 00:23:58.000
WHY THEY'D BEEN THERE

00:23:58.000 --> 00:24:00.000
THAT IT WAS NOT
ONLY A ROCK CONCERT

00:24:00.000 --> 00:24:04.000
IT WAS A REMEMBRANCE OF SOMEBODY
THAT WAS IN PRISON

00:24:04.000 --> 00:24:05.000
FOR THE WRONG REASON.

00:24:05.000 --> 00:24:23.000
* ...AND GRACE
MY FEARS RELIEVED *

00:24:23.000 --> 00:24:27.000
* HOW PRECIOUS... *

00:24:27.000 --> 00:24:30.000
THERE IS A POWER
OF RECONCILIATION

00:24:30.000 --> 00:24:33.000
THAT TAKES PLACE WHEN I HEAR IT.

00:24:33.000 --> 00:24:35.000
I DON'T KNOW WHETHER
IT'S THE TEXT

00:24:35.000 --> 00:24:38.000
WHETHER WE'RE TALKING
ABOUT THE LYRICS

00:24:38.000 --> 00:24:41.000
WHEN WE SAY THAT
IT TOUCHES SO MANY PEOPLE

00:24:41.000 --> 00:24:45.000
OR WHETHER IT'S THAT TUNE
THAT EVERYBODY KNOWS

00:24:45.000 --> 00:24:48.000
AND EVEN THE MELODY
HAS CHANGED A LITTLE BIT.

00:24:48.000 --> 00:24:51.000
WHEN I SING IT, I TRY TO SING IT

00:24:51.000 --> 00:24:53.000
THE WAY IT WAS PUBLISHED
ABOUT 1900

00:24:53.000 --> 00:24:57.000
BUT THE MELODY ITSELF HAS HAD
SOME VARIATIONS AS WELL.

00:24:57.000 --> 00:25:01.000
THE WAY IT WAS
WRITTEN WE HAVE

00:25:01.000 --> 00:25:07.000
* AMAZING GRACE!
HOW SWEET THE SOUND *

00:25:07.000 --> 00:25:09.000
* THAT SAVED... *

00:25:10.000 --> 00:25:12.000
ALL OF THAT IS REALLY
QUITE STRAIGHT

00:25:12.000 --> 00:25:14.000
BUT I THINK BY THE TIME,
IN THE '60s

00:25:14.000 --> 00:25:16.000
WHEN JUDY COLLINS WAS DOING IT

00:25:17.000 --> 00:25:19.000
IT TOOK ON AN EVEN MORE
LYRICAL QUALITY.

00:25:19.000 --> 00:25:25.000
* AMAZING GRACE!
HOW SWEET THE SOUND *

00:25:25.000 --> 00:25:29.000
* THAT SAVED A WRETCH LIKE ME. *

00:25:30.000 --> 00:25:34.000
ALL OF THESE LOVELY MOVING NOTES
IN BETWEEN THE ORIGINAL MELODY.

00:25:34.000 --> 00:25:35.000
HAVE YOU EVER HEARD

00:25:36.000 --> 00:25:38.000
ANY SHAPE NOTE SINGERS SING IT?

00:25:38.000 --> 00:25:40.000
IT'S REALLY QUITE SOMETHING.

00:25:40.000 --> 00:25:42.000
I CAN'T IMITATE THAT.

00:25:42.000 --> 00:25:43.000
IT'S SOMETHING PRIMAL.

00:25:43.000 --> 00:25:46.000
IT BECOMES SOMETHING
THAT'S REALLY COMING

00:25:46.000 --> 00:25:48.000
FROM THE CENTER OF THE EARTH.

00:25:48.000 --> 00:25:53.000
( Churchmembers singing )

00:26:15.000 --> 00:26:20.000
( harmonized singing )

00:26:23.000 --> 00:26:33.000
* AMAZING GRACE!
HOW SWEET THE SOUND *

00:26:33.000 --> 00:26:40.000
* THAT SAVED A WRETCH LIKE ME. *

00:26:40.000 --> 00:26:44.000
Man:
I WOULD THINK THAT WHEN THEY
FIRST INTRODUCED "AMAZING GRACE"

00:26:44.000 --> 00:26:47.000
THEY'D SING JUST LIKE
WE SING IT TODAY.

00:26:47.000 --> 00:26:49.000
WE SING IT JUST LIKE IT WAS SUNG

00:26:49.000 --> 00:26:52.000
WHEN IT WAS FIRST PUT
IN THE BOOK 150 YEARS AGO.

00:26:52.000 --> 00:26:57.000
* ...BUT NOW I SEE. *

00:26:57.000 --> 00:26:59.000
100 YEARS AGO,
JUST ABOUT ALL YOU HAD

00:26:59.000 --> 00:27:01.000
THROUGH THIS WHOLE COUNTRY HERE

00:27:02.000 --> 00:27:03.000
WAS SHAPE NOTES.

00:27:03.000 --> 00:27:06.000
THERE WASN'T ANYTHING ELSE.

00:27:06.000 --> 00:27:08.000
THERE WASN'T A LOT OF PEOPLE

00:27:08.000 --> 00:27:11.000
DOWN IN RURAL SECTIONS OF
THE COUNTRY 150 YEARS AGO

00:27:11.000 --> 00:27:14.000
AND WHEN YOU HAD
AN ALL-DAY SINGING

00:27:14.000 --> 00:27:18.000
YOU'D JUST ABOUT GET THE WHOLE
TOWN AND THE WHOLE COMMUNITY.

00:27:18.000 --> 00:27:21.000
"AMAZING GRACE" HAS BEEN
JUST ABOUT USED THE SAME WAY

00:27:21.000 --> 00:27:24.000
SINCE THE START
OF PUTTING IT IN BOOKS.

00:27:29.000 --> 00:27:34.000
THE SHAPES WASN'T INVENTED
UNTIL 1798 BY SMITH AND LITTLE.

00:27:34.000 --> 00:27:38.000
THEY WROTE A BOOK AND THEY SAID
"FA" WILL BE TRIANGULAR

00:27:38.000 --> 00:27:41.000
"SO" WILL BE ROUND,
"LA" WILL BE SQUARE

00:27:41.000 --> 00:27:43.000
AND "ME" WILL BE DIAMOND SHAPED.

00:27:43.000 --> 00:27:45.000
AND THEN THEY STARTED
SINGING SHAPED NOTES

00:27:45.000 --> 00:27:47.000
ALL OVER THE COUNTRY
IN SINGING SCHOOLS

00:27:47.000 --> 00:27:50.000
BECAUSE IT WAS THE EASIEST
METHOD IN THE WORLD

00:27:50.000 --> 00:27:53.000
FOR BEGINNERS TO LEARN TO SING.

00:27:53.000 --> 00:27:56.000
IF YOU PUT SEVEN ROUND
NOTES ON A SCALE

00:27:56.000 --> 00:27:58.000
IT'S HARD TO GET
THE SOUND OF THEM

00:27:58.000 --> 00:28:01.000
WITHOUT SOME KIND
OF INSTRUMENT TO HELP YOU.

00:28:01.000 --> 00:28:05.000
HERE, YOU CAN START OUT
WITH YOUR FA-SO-LA-ME

00:28:05.000 --> 00:28:08.000
YOU GO UP AND YOU'D FIND OUT
THE SOUND OF IT

00:28:08.000 --> 00:28:11.000
AND TODAY WE STILL SING
THE SHAPES FIRST

00:28:11.000 --> 00:28:15.000
BECAUSE THEY'VE BECOME
A TRADITION WITH US.

00:28:15.000 --> 00:28:20.000
( group finishes singing )

00:28:20.000 --> 00:28:22.000
EVERYBODY IS INVITED OUT
TO DINNER ON THE TABLE

00:28:22.000 --> 00:28:26.000
AND IF YOU'VE GOT DINNER
THAT YOU WANT TO SPREAD WITH US

00:28:26.000 --> 00:28:28.000
BE SURE TO SPREAD IT OUT WITH US

00:28:28.000 --> 00:28:30.000
AND WE'LL HELP YOU EAT IT UP.

00:28:30.000 --> 00:28:32.000
EVERYBODY DISMISSED
FOR ABOUT ONE HOUR.

00:28:32.000 --> 00:28:36.000
THAT WAS A REAL GOOD APPROPRIATE
TIME FOR YOU TO SING THAT.

00:28:36.000 --> 00:28:38.000
IT WAS REAL GOOD.

00:28:38.000 --> 00:28:39.000
IT SURE WAS GOOD.

00:28:44.000 --> 00:28:47.000
MY FAMILY ALWAYS SANG
IN SACRED HARP

00:28:47.000 --> 00:28:50.000
AND I JUST GREW UP SINGING
SACRED HARP

00:28:50.000 --> 00:28:55.000
AND I'VE BEEN COMING HERE SINCE
I CAN REMEMBER AS A SMALL CHILD.

00:28:55.000 --> 00:28:57.000
WE COME TWICE A YEAR UP HERE.

00:28:57.000 --> 00:29:00.000
WE HAVE ONE IN JUNE
AND THEN ONE IN NOVEMBER

00:29:01.000 --> 00:29:02.000
BUT THEY'RE ALL OVER.

00:29:02.000 --> 00:29:04.000
WE GO ABOUT EVERY SUNDAY.

00:29:04.000 --> 00:29:09.000
I THINK IT'S THE FEELING
THAT YOU HAVE, THE TRADITION

00:29:09.000 --> 00:29:12.000
AND IT'S TIED IN
WITH YOUR FAMILIES.

00:29:12.000 --> 00:29:15.000
THERE'S A LOT OF GOOD MEMORIES.

00:29:15.000 --> 00:29:20.000
BUT THEN, WE WORSHIP THE LORD
IN SONG, AND I LIKE THAT.

00:29:20.000 --> 00:29:24.000
THEY SING "AMAZING GRACE"
A LOT IN THIS SINGING

00:29:24.000 --> 00:29:25.000
AND ALL SINGINGS.

00:29:25.000 --> 00:29:28.000
AND IT'S BEAUTIFUL EVERYWHERE.

00:29:28.000 --> 00:29:30.000
Man:
IT'S JUST A GOOD SONG.

00:29:30.000 --> 00:29:34.000
IT'S WROTE LIKE
IT'S SUPPOSED TO BE WROTE.

00:29:34.000 --> 00:29:39.000
McGraw:
"AMAZING GRACE" IS NOT THE NAME
OF THE SONG IN OUR BOOK.

00:29:40.000 --> 00:29:42.000
IT'S NAMED "NEW BRITAIN."

00:29:42.000 --> 00:29:45.000
WE DON'T KNOW
WHERE THE TUNE COME FROM.

00:29:45.000 --> 00:29:48.000
WE'VE COME TO THE CONCLUSION
THAT IT WAS A BALLAD

00:29:48.000 --> 00:29:51.000
THAT WAS SUNG MANY,
MANY YEARS AGO

00:29:51.000 --> 00:29:53.000
IN SOME OF THE OLD COUNTRIES

00:29:53.000 --> 00:29:55.000
AND SOMEBODY HAS
TAKEN THE BALLAD

00:29:55.000 --> 00:29:58.000
AND PUT THE WORDS OF
"AMAZING GRACE" TO IT.

00:29:58.000 --> 00:30:03.000
IT'S MORE THAN JUST A SOUND,
IT'S THE FELLOWSHIP AND THE LOVE

00:30:03.000 --> 00:30:06.000
THAT WE HAVE FOR ONE ANOTHER

00:30:06.000 --> 00:30:11.000
THAT MAKES US SING OUR HEARTS
OUT FOR ONE ANOTHER.

00:30:27.000 --> 00:30:34.000
( people singing
 "Amazing Grace" )

00:30:34.000 --> 00:30:37.000
McGraw:
THEY'S ANOTHER GROUP
THAT SINGS SHAPE NOTES

00:30:37.000 --> 00:30:39.000
DOWN IN SOUTH ALABAMA

00:30:39.000 --> 00:30:41.000
CALLED BLACK SACRED HEART.

00:30:41.000 --> 00:30:44.000
THEY ACTLLY CALL THEIRSELF
THE "WIREGRASS SINGERS"

00:30:44.000 --> 00:30:49.000
AND DEWEY WILLIAMS,
HE LEADS THE SINGING.

00:30:49.000 --> 00:30:59.000
Man:
* WAS BLIND... BUT NOW... *

00:30:59.000 --> 00:31:07.000
* WAS BLIND, BUT NOW I SEE. *

00:31:07.000 --> 00:31:12.000
AND WHEN YOU WANT
TO SING IT ANOTHER WAY.

00:31:12.000 --> 00:31:19.000
* AMAZING GRACE!
HOW SWEET THE SOUND *

00:31:19.000 --> 00:31:26.000
* THAT SAVED A WRETCH LIKE ME *

00:31:26.000 --> 00:31:33.000
* I ONCE WAS LOST,
BUT NOW I'M FOUND *

00:31:33.000 --> 00:31:38.000
* WAS BLIND, BUT NOW I SEE. *

00:31:38.000 --> 00:31:41.000
THAT'S JUST AS TRUE AS THE DAY.

00:31:41.000 --> 00:31:48.000
* THROUGH MANY DANGERS,
TOILS AND SNARES *

