* AMAZING GRACE!
HOW SWEET... *

00:43:02.000 --> 00:43:05.000
Moyers:
DO YOU REFLECT ON
THAT FIRST TIME YOU SANG

00:43:05.000 --> 00:43:08.000
AT THE HUNTSVILLE PRISON IN '57?

00:43:08.000 --> 00:43:10.000
Cash:
OH, YEAH, I SURE DO.

00:43:10.000 --> 00:43:13.000
THAT WAS MY FIRST PRISON
CONCERT AT HUNTSVILLE.

00:43:13.000 --> 00:43:20.000
* I ONCE WAS LOST,
BUT NOW I'M FOUND... *

00:43:20.000 --> 00:43:23.000
Cash:
FOR THAT THREE MINUTES
THAT SONG IS GOING ON

00:43:23.000 --> 00:43:26.000
EVERYBODY IS FREE,
AND IT JUST FREES THE SPIRIT.

00:43:26.000 --> 00:43:29.000
Prisoner:
* ...LIKE ME... *

00:43:29.000 --> 00:43:40.000
* I ONCE WAS LOST,
BUT NOW I'M FOUND *

00:43:40.000 --> 00:43:46.000
* WAS BLIND, BUT NOW I SEE. *

00:43:46.000 --> 00:43:49.000
Man:
I'VE BEEN LOCKED UP
HALF MY LIFE.

00:43:49.000 --> 00:43:54.000
I'VE SEEN AND DONE JUST ABOUT
ANYTHING YOU CAN IMAGINE.

00:43:54.000 --> 00:43:57.000
I CAME IN HERE FOR THAT.

00:43:57.000 --> 00:43:59.000
HOW MUCH LONGER
ARE YOU GOING
TO BE HERE?

00:43:59.000 --> 00:44:02.000
WHO KNOWS?-- THAT'S IRRELEVANT
RIGHT NOW, ANYWAY.

00:44:02.000 --> 00:44:04.000
I'M DEALING WITH DAY TO DAY.

00:44:04.000 --> 00:44:07.000
I DON'T WORRY ABOUT
NEXT WEEK OR NEXT YEAR.

00:44:07.000 --> 00:44:09.000
WHAT ARE YOU
IN HERE FOR?

00:44:09.000 --> 00:44:13.000
MURDER, DRUGS, ARMED ROBBERY,
BURGLARY OF A HOUSE AT NIGHT

00:44:13.000 --> 00:44:15.000
AND...

00:44:15.000 --> 00:44:16.000
I WAS A REAL IDIOT.

00:44:16.000 --> 00:44:18.000
ONCE IT STARTED,
IT WAS JUST

00:44:18.000 --> 00:44:19.000
ONE THING
AFTER ANOTHER.

00:44:19.000 --> 00:44:25.000
I ENDED UP IN A LOCKUP--
IN THAT SOLITARY OVER THERE

00:44:25.000 --> 00:44:29.000
AND I WAS THINKING,
"BOY, YOU IDIOT," YOU KNOW.

00:44:29.000 --> 00:44:32.000
YOU THOUGHT YOU WERE
SO SMART, YOU KNOW.

00:44:32.000 --> 00:44:36.000
ALL THESE YEARS, MAN, YOU'VE
BEEN PLAYING IT SO CLEVER

00:44:36.000 --> 00:44:40.000
AND THEN, YOU KNOW,
LOOK WHERE YOU'RE AT NOW.

00:44:40.000 --> 00:44:42.000
YOU'RE NEVER GOING
TO GET OUT OF HERE.

00:44:42.000 --> 00:44:45.000
YOU'RE NEVER
GETTING OUT OF HERE.

00:44:45.000 --> 00:44:47.000
AND ALMOST
IMMEDIATELY

00:44:47.000 --> 00:44:51.000
THE WORDS TO "AMAZING GRACE"
BECAME REAL TO ME.

00:44:52.000 --> 00:44:54.000
I COULDN'T HARDLY
SING THAT SONG

00:44:54.000 --> 00:44:57.000
AND GET THROUGH
FOUR VERSES OF IT
WITHOUT CHOKING UP.

00:44:57.000 --> 00:45:00.000
I COULD GET THROUGH
ABOUT THE SECOND VERSE

00:45:00.000 --> 00:45:03.000
AND I WOULD START
KIND OF LOCKING UP

00:45:03.000 --> 00:45:05.000
AND A LOT OF TIMES,
ALL I COULD DO

00:45:05.000 --> 00:45:07.000
IS JUST BE HUMMING AND CRYING

00:45:07.000 --> 00:45:10.000
BECAUSE IT'S A REAL SONG
EVEN NOW TO ME.

00:45:10.000 --> 00:45:13.000
IT HAS TO BE TAKEN
IN AN OVERALL VIEW

00:45:13.000 --> 00:45:17.000
BUT PROBABLY THE MOST
FAVORITE LINES TO ME

00:45:17.000 --> 00:45:21.000
THAT MEANS SOMETHING TO ME NOW
ARE THE SECOND VERSE

00:45:21.000 --> 00:45:25.000
WHERE IT'S TALKING ABOUT
THAT GRACE CAUSED YOU TO FEAR

00:45:25.000 --> 00:45:28.000
AND AT FIRST YOU THINK
THAT DOESN'T MAKE SENSE

00:45:29.000 --> 00:45:33.000
BUT WHEN YOU COME IN HERE AND
YOU TAKE A LOOK, YOU DO FEAR.

00:45:33.000 --> 00:45:35.000
YOU GET SO AFRAID
THAT YOU'RE NOT GOING

00:45:36.000 --> 00:45:38.000
TO GET YOUR LIFE
IN ORDER IN TIME.

00:45:38.000 --> 00:45:41.000
IT'S A FEAR THAT IS HARD
TO PUT INTO WORDS

00:45:41.000 --> 00:45:42.000
OF BEING ALONE

00:45:42.000 --> 00:45:46.000
OF BEING LOCKED IN
WHEN YOU'RE USED TO BEING FREE.

00:45:46.000 --> 00:45:49.000
Moyers:
IN THOSE CIRCUMSTANCES,
AMAZING GRACE IS NO WAY OUT.

00:45:49.000 --> 00:45:51.000
IT WON'T UNLOCK THOSE BARS.

00:45:52.000 --> 00:45:55.000
Man:
NO, BUT THAT'S YOUR ONLY CHANCE.

00:45:55.000 --> 00:45:56.000
THE ONLY WAY OUT IS UP.

00:45:56.000 --> 00:45:59.000
Moyers:
SOME PEOPLE WILL
FIND IT DIFFICULT

00:45:59.000 --> 00:46:01.000
TO BELIEVE THAT
HARDENED MEN

00:46:01.000 --> 00:46:03.000
WOULD BE AFFECTED
BY SUCH A SONG

00:46:03.000 --> 00:46:05.000
AND THEY'LL BE
VERY SKEPTICAL.

00:46:06.000 --> 00:46:08.000
THEY'LL SAY,
"IT'S A RELIGIOUS SPASM.

00:46:08.000 --> 00:46:11.000
IT'S NOTHING BUT PIETY,
NOTHING BUT SENTIMENT."

00:46:11.000 --> 00:46:16.000
YOU KNOW, BILL, WE HAVE HAD
AN OPPORTUNITY AND A CHANCE

00:46:16.000 --> 00:46:18.000
TO FACE OUR TRANSGRESSIONS.

00:46:18.000 --> 00:46:21.000
WE HAVE A LOT OF TIME
TO THINK ABOUT IT.

00:46:21.000 --> 00:46:22.000
WE'VE BEEN
RECONCILED.

00:46:22.000 --> 00:46:24.000
WE HAVE
A PEACE INSIDE.

00:46:24.000 --> 00:46:26.000
WH ARE YOU
IN HERE FOR?

00:46:26.000 --> 00:46:29.000
I'M HERE FOR SOLICITATION
OF CAPITAL MURDER--

00:46:30.000 --> 00:46:33.000
TRYING TO ARRANGE
FOR HAVING MY WIFE KILLED.

00:46:33.000 --> 00:46:36.000
WHEN DID YOU
FIRST UNDERSTAND

00:46:36.000 --> 00:46:39.000
THE MEANING OF
"AMAZING GRACE"?

00:46:39.000 --> 00:46:43.000
THAT WAS IN NOVEMBER OF 1987
WHEN I GOT HERE.

00:46:43.000 --> 00:46:45.000
( Moyers
 laughs )

00:46:45.000 --> 00:46:47.000
THIS IS WHY I CAN SPEAK

00:46:47.000 --> 00:46:49.000
BECAUSE I WAS ONE
OF THESE CHURCH CROWDS

00:46:50.000 --> 00:46:53.000
WHO'D NEVER REALIZED THE
TRUE MEANING OF "AMAZING GRACE."

00:46:53.000 --> 00:46:55.000
I WAS HIDING
BEHIND IT.

00:46:55.000 --> 00:46:58.000
I WAS
VERY INVOLVED
IN THE CHURCH.

00:46:58.000 --> 00:47:00.000
I WAS A DEACON
IN THE BAPTIST CHURCH.

00:47:01.000 --> 00:47:02.000
I SANG IN THE CHOIR...

00:47:02.000 --> 00:47:05.000
AND YOU TRIED
TO HAVE YOUR
WIFE KILLED?

00:47:05.000 --> 00:47:06.000
YES, I DID.

00:47:06.000 --> 00:47:09.000
SO WHAT'S YOUR FAVORITE VERSE?

00:47:09.000 --> 00:47:13.000
"THROUGH MANY TRIALS
AND TOILS AND SNARES

00:47:13.000 --> 00:47:17.000
IT'S GRACE THAT'S BEEN VERY..."
THE THIRD VERSE.

00:47:17.000 --> 00:47:19.000
THOSE WORDS IN THEMSELF
HOLD A STORY

00:47:19.000 --> 00:47:23.000
FOR A GENERATION OF PEOPLE,
IF THEY'LL JUST LISTEN.

00:47:23.000 --> 00:47:26.000
* ...HOW SWEET THE SOUND *

00:47:26.000 --> 00:47:33.000
* THAT SAVED A WRETCH LIKE ME *

00:47:34.000 --> 00:47:43.000
* I ONCE WAS LOST, *
BUT NOW I'M FOUND *

00:47:43.000 --> 00:47:51.000
* WAS BLIND, BUT NOW I SEE *

00:47:51.000 --> 00:48:01.000
* 'TWAS GRACE THAT TAUGHT
MY HEART TO FEAR *

00:48:01.000 --> 00:48:10.000
* AND GRACE MY FEARS RELIEVED *

00:48:10.000 --> 00:48:19.000
* HOW PRECIOUS DID
THAT GRACE APPEAR *

00:48:19.000 --> 00:48:30.000
* THE HOUR I FIRST BELIEVED. *

00:48:30.000 --> 00:48:34.000
AS A SONGWRITER, YOU KNOW
WHAT I THINK ABOUT THAT SONG--

00:48:34.000 --> 00:48:38.000
AS A SONGWRITER, OBJECTIVELY--
THERE IS A SONG WITH NO GUILE.

00:48:38.000 --> 00:48:41.000
THOSE LYRICS ARE STRAIGHT AHEAD

00:48:41.000 --> 00:48:44.000
HONEST, GUT LEVEL,
AND HEART LEVEL.

00:48:44.000 --> 00:48:50.000
* ...BRIGHT SHINING AS THE SUN *

00:48:50.000 --> 00:48:57.000
* WE'VE NO LESS DAYS
TO SING GOD'S PRAISE *

00:48:57.000 --> 00:49:03.000
* THAN WHEN WE FIRST BEGUN. *

00:49:03.000 --> 00:49:06.000
WHEN I SING THAT SONG
I COULD BE IN A DUNGEON

00:49:06.000 --> 00:49:09.000
OR HAVE
CHAINS ALL OVER ME

00:49:09.000 --> 00:49:11.000
BUT I'D BE FREE AS A BREEZE.

00:49:11.000 --> 00:49:15.000
THERE ARE SOME SONGS THAT MAKE
A DIFFERENCE IN YOUR LIFE

00:49:15.000 --> 00:49:18.000
AND THAT SONG MAKES
A DIFFERENCE.

00:49:24.000 --> 00:49:29.000
( boys humming the scale )

00:49:37.000 --> 00:49:42.000
Man:
IF YOU SEE ANY CHILD
WHO IS JUST PASSING TIME

00:49:42.000 --> 00:49:46.000
MOST WOULD LIKE TO SING
OR LISTEN TO MUSIC

00:49:46.000 --> 00:49:50.000
OR IN THIS DAY AND AGE,
RAP, SO THERE IS A...

00:49:50.000 --> 00:49:56.000
THERE'S A CERTAIN MEANS OF
EXPRESSION THAT'S GOOD FOR THEM

00:49:56.000 --> 00:49:59.000
AND THEY FEEL VERY GOOD
ABOUT THAT.

00:49:59.000 --> 00:50:05.000
( humming continues )

00:50:05.000 --> 00:50:11.000
IT'S A WAY TO EXPRESS,
TO COME FROM THE INNER SOUL

00:50:11.000 --> 00:50:15.000
AND I THINK THAT THAT'S
VERY IMPORTANT.

00:50:17.000 --> 00:50:19.000
Turnbull:
ALL THE WAY
FROM THE TOP.

00:50:19.000 --> 00:50:24.000
SIT UP, IF YOU'RE
SITTING, OKAY?

00:50:24.000 --> 00:50:27.000
( piano introduction )

00:50:30.000 --> 00:50:38.000
( boys humming "Amazing Grace" )

00:50:56.000 --> 00:51:00.000
IT'S STILL GOT TO BE ON PITCH,
TREBLES, WHEN YOU COME BACK

00:51:00.000 --> 00:51:02.000
SO KEEP
THE SUPPORT UP
UNDER IT.

00:51:02.000 --> 00:51:04.000
EVERYBODY, JUST
GENERALLY WARMER.

00:51:04.000 --> 00:51:06.000
ALL RIGHT, SAME THING, PLEASE.

00:51:07.000 --> 00:51:08.000
VERY LEGATO.

00:51:08.000 --> 00:51:15.000
I'M THINKING CALM,
SMOOTH... MEDITIVE.

00:51:15.000 --> 00:51:17.000
YOU KNOW?

00:51:17.000 --> 00:51:19.000
READY, AND...

00:51:22.000 --> 00:51:25.000
Turnbull:
IT SORT OF GOES BACK TO, I THINK

00:51:25.000 --> 00:51:29.000
TO MY EXPERIENCES
AS A CHILD IN MISSISSIPPI--

00:51:29.000 --> 00:51:31.000
I GREW UP IN GREENVILLE,
MISSISSIPPI.

00:51:32.000 --> 00:51:35.000
I GOT A CHOIR SCHOLARSHIP
TO GO TO COLLEGE

00:51:35.000 --> 00:51:38.000
WHICH WAS THE ONLY WAY
TO GO TO COLLEGE

00:51:38.000 --> 00:51:40.000
AND I SANG MY WAY
THROUGH COLLEGE.

00:51:40.000 --> 00:51:42.000
BEING INVOLVED IN THE CHURCH

00:51:42.000 --> 00:51:45.000
BEING INVOLVED IN CHOIR
ALL MY LIFE

00:51:45.000 --> 00:51:48.000
I DECIDED TO GET
A GROUP OF KIDS TOGETHER.

00:51:48.000 --> 00:51:51.000
BY THAT TIME,
I HAD BEGUN TO TEACH

00:51:51.000 --> 00:51:54.000
IN THE NEW YORK CITY
PUBLIC SCHOOLS AS WELL

00:51:54.000 --> 00:51:57.000
AND IT SORT OF ALL CAME TOGETHER

00:51:57.000 --> 00:52:01.000
BECAUSE I FOUND THAT WORKING
WITH CHILDREN IN TERMS OF CHOIR

00:52:01.000 --> 00:52:04.000
AND THEM FEELING GOOD
ABOUT THEMSELVES

00:52:04.000 --> 00:52:07.000
REALLY MADE THEM DO
EXCITING THINGS OTHERWISE.

00:52:07.000 --> 00:52:17.000
* ...I ONCE WAS LOST,
BUT NOW I'M FOUND *

00:52:17.000 --> 00:52:22.000
* WAS BLIND, BUT NOW I SEE. *

00:52:22.000 --> 00:52:25.000
Turnbull:
THERE'S NO
BREATH, PLEASE!

00:52:25.000 --> 00:52:28.000
THAT'S NOT IT,
COME ON, THAT'S
NOT IT!

00:52:28.000 --> 00:52:31.000
Boy:
WELL, THEY AUDITIONED
ME AT MY SCHOOL

00:52:31.000 --> 00:52:32.000
AND OUT OF A LOT OF BOYS

00:52:32.000 --> 00:52:35.000
IT WAS ONLY A GROUP
OF US THAT MADE IT

00:52:35.000 --> 00:52:39.000
AND OUT OF THAT GROUP,
THEY CAME TO THE CHOIR EVERY DAY

00:52:39.000 --> 00:52:41.000
AND SOME DAYS THEY PICKED US UP

00:52:41.000 --> 00:52:45.000
BUT MOST OF THE BOYS
THAT CAME IN WITH ME QUIT.

00:52:45.000 --> 00:52:48.000
I'M THE ONLY ONE
FROM MY SCHOOL THAT STAYED.

00:52:48.000 --> 00:52:50.000
I WAS A LITTLE
TRAINING TROUBLE

00:52:50.000 --> 00:52:53.000
BECAUSE I STILL WASN'T
INTO THE CHOIR THAT MUCH.

00:52:53.000 --> 00:52:55.000
SO I WAS LIKE "AMAZING GRACE"--

00:52:55.000 --> 00:52:58.000
I HEARD OF IT BUT I DIDN'T
REALLY UNDERSTAND IT

00:52:58.000 --> 00:52:59.000
AND IT'S KIND OF HARD.

00:52:59.000 --> 00:53:02.000
AT THE BEGINNING
OF "AMAZING GRACE"

00:53:02.000 --> 00:53:03.000
THERE'S A LOT OF "OOHS"

00:53:03.000 --> 00:53:07.000
AND YOU HAVE TO HAVE A LOT
OF BREATH SUPPORT-- KEEP IT UP

00:53:07.000 --> 00:53:11.000
AND WHEN YOU KEEP YOUR MOUTH
IN THIS KIND OF POSITION

00:53:11.000 --> 00:53:13.000
IT KIND OF HURTS
AROUND YOUR MOUTH

00:53:13.000 --> 00:53:15.000
SO THAT'S WHY I SAY IT'S HARD.

00:53:15.000 --> 00:53:19.000
WE USUALLY SING EVERY YEAR
AT AARON DAVIS HALL

00:53:19.000 --> 00:53:23.000
AND THE FIRST TIME THE CHOIR
HAD JUST CAME IN FROM OFF A TOUR

00:53:23.000 --> 00:53:28.000
AND WE WAS GOING TO MEET
THE PARENTS AT AARON DAVIS HALL

00:53:28.000 --> 00:53:32.000
AND WHEN WE GOT INTO
THE POP SHOW AFTER THE CLASSICAL

00:53:32.000 --> 00:53:35.000
WE CAME OUT AND WE STARTED
SINGING "AMAZING GRACE"

00:53:35.000 --> 00:53:37.000
AND MY MOTHER STARTED
CRYING AFTER

00:53:38.000 --> 00:53:41.000
AND I WAS LIKE, I SAID,
"MA, WHY ARE YOU CRYING?" RIGHT.

00:53:41.000 --> 00:53:45.000
AND SHE SAID, "I'M NOT CRYING
BECAUSE NOTHING BAD HAPPENED."

00:53:45.000 --> 00:53:49.000
SHE WAS CRYING BECAUSE
SHE WAS HAPPY AND JOYFUL

00:53:49.000 --> 00:53:52.000
AND EVERYTHING LIKE THAT,
BECAUSE SHE SAID TO ME

00:53:52.000 --> 00:53:56.000
THAT IT BRINGS BACK MEMORIES
FROM A LONG, LONG TIME AGO

00:53:56.000 --> 00:53:59.000
SO I WAS HAPPY
TO SING IT FOR HER

00:53:59.000 --> 00:54:02.000
AND ALL THE OTHER PEOPLE
IN THE AUDIENCE.

00:54:03.000 --> 00:54:06.000
Turnbull:
"AMAZING GRACE" IS ONE
OF THE VERY POPULAR SONGS

00:54:06.000 --> 00:54:08.000
IN OUR REPERTOIRE

00:54:08.000 --> 00:54:11.000
AND WE'LL BE DOING IT IN JAPAN,
SINGING IT IN JAPAN.

00:54:12.000 --> 00:54:14.000
NO-- CARRY THROUGH
"LORD," PLEASE!

00:54:19.000 --> 00:54:21.000
PITCHES, AGAIN, PLEASE.

00:54:21.000 --> 00:54:22.000
( piano plays )

00:54:22.000 --> 00:54:24.000
ONE, TWO!

00:54:24.000 --> 00:54:26.000
( boys resume singing )

00:54:26.000 --> 00:54:29.000
Turnbull:
I THINK IT'S IMPORTANT

00:54:29.000 --> 00:54:33.000
THAT IT PLAYS A ROLE IN THEIR
LIVES OTHER THAN JUST SINGING

00:54:33.000 --> 00:54:36.000
BECAUSE THE SINGING IS
THE DISCIPLINE.

00:54:36.000 --> 00:54:40.000
THE MUSIC IS THE DISCIPLINE
WHEREBY THE COMMON GOAL

00:54:40.000 --> 00:54:42.000
THAT WE HAVE FOR THE KIDS

00:54:42.000 --> 00:54:45.000
AND THEN FROM THAT,
THEY LEARN ALL KINDS OF THINGS

00:54:45.000 --> 00:54:48.000
WHICH HELPS THEM IN THEIR LIFE.

00:54:48.000 --> 00:54:51.000
WE HAVE SOME BOYS, MEN NOW,
WHO HAVE BECOME DOCTORS

00:54:51.000 --> 00:54:54.000
LAWYERS, STOCKBROKERS,
TEACHERS, PREACHERS

00:54:55.000 --> 00:54:58.000
AND THE COMMONNESS THROUGH THAT
IS THE DISCIPLINE

00:54:58.000 --> 00:55:00.000
THE STICK-TO-IT-IVENESS

00:55:00.000 --> 00:55:03.000
THE ABILITY TO SET A GOAL
AND REACH IT.

00:55:07.000 --> 00:55:09.000
( boys shouting )

00:55:09.000 --> 00:55:13.000
Boy:
I FEEL DIFFERENT FROM
THE REGULAR KIDS ON THE BLOCK

00:55:13.000 --> 00:55:16.000
BECAUSE I'M GOING AWAY;
I'M GETTING TO SEE THINGS

00:55:17.000 --> 00:55:21.000
THAT KIDS DON'T GET A CHANCE
TO SEE-- NOT MOST OF THEM.

00:55:21.000 --> 00:55:23.000
I DON'T REALLY GET TO PLAY A LOT

00:55:23.000 --> 00:55:27.000
BECAUSE I'M MOSTLY WITH
THE CHOIR SATURDAY AND SUNDAY

00:55:28.000 --> 00:55:29.000
TRAVELING SOMEWHERE.

00:55:29.000 --> 00:55:33.000
AND I JUST THINK I HAVE A
DIFFERENT LIFE THAN REGULAR KIDS

00:55:34.000 --> 00:55:36.000
EXCEPT FOR THE KIDS
IN THE CHOIR.

00:55:36.000 --> 00:55:38.000
I THINK WE ALL HAVE
THE SAME LIFE

00:55:38.000 --> 00:55:40.000
BUT THE KIDS OUT ON THE STREET

00:55:40.000 --> 00:55:43.000
DON'T THINK WE DO
HAVE THE SAME LIFE.

00:55:55.000 --> 00:55:56.000
( plays a wrong note )

00:55:56.000 --> 00:55:57.000
IF YOU WROTE THIS

00:55:57.000 --> 00:55:59.000
FOR AN ORCHESTRA

00:55:59.000 --> 00:56:01.000
WHAT INSTRUMENT
MIGHT PLAY THIS?

00:56:01.000 --> 00:56:03.000
IT'S AN
INTRODUCTION, RIGHT?

00:56:04.000 --> 00:56:05.000
PROBABLY TRUMPETS?

00:56:05.000 --> 00:56:07.000
YEAH, SURE--
LIKE A FANFARE.

00:56:08.000 --> 00:56:09.000
( mimics a trumpet )

00:56:09.000 --> 00:56:11.000
OKAY, CAN YOU MAKE THE PIANO

00:56:11.000 --> 00:56:14.000
SOUND MORE LIKE A TRUMPET
AT THE BEGINNING?

00:56:14.000 --> 00:56:15.000
OKAY, I'LL TRY.

00:56:15.000 --> 00:56:17.000
( short, rhythmic notes )

00:56:18.000 --> 00:56:22.000
Boy:
THERE WAS ONE PERIOD OF TIME
WHEN I USED TO NOT COME.

00:56:22.000 --> 00:56:25.000
I USED TO TELL MY MOTHER
I WAS GOING TO THE CHOIR

00:56:25.000 --> 00:56:29.000
BUT I WOULD GO HOME AND SIT ON
THE STAIRS AND DO MY HOMEWORK.

00:56:30.000 --> 00:56:33.000
THEN LIKE, AFTER THEY GOT
OUT OF REHEARSAL

00:56:33.000 --> 00:56:37.000
THEN I'LL WAIT A WHILE,
AND THEN I'LL GO HOME.

00:56:37.000 --> 00:56:39.000
I JUST-- WELL,
THEY GOT ON MY CASE.

00:56:39.000 --> 00:56:42.000
I HAD TO TALK TO ONE
OF THE COUNSELORS.

00:56:42.000 --> 00:56:45.000
THEY KNEW I WAS LYING,
KIND OF, LIKE

00:56:45.000 --> 00:56:49.000
AND SO I CLEANED UP MY ACT
AND I STARTED COMING

00:56:49.000 --> 00:56:51.000
AND I STARTED LIKING IT.

00:56:53.000 --> 00:56:55.000
Woman:
HE MIGHT CALL IT PECULIAR.

00:56:55.000 --> 00:57:00.000
HE MIGHT SAY THAT HE'S PECULIAR,
HE'S DIFFERENT THAN OTHER KIDS.

00:57:00.000 --> 00:57:02.000
HE'S ALWAYS SAID THAT.

00:57:02.000 --> 00:57:06.000
HE NEVER USED THE WORD "GRACE"
BECAUSE I GUESS AT TEN

00:57:06.000 --> 00:57:10.000
HE CAN'T DEFINE THE FEELING,
BUT HE SAYS HE'S PECULIAR

00:57:10.000 --> 00:57:12.000
AND I TELL HIM HE'S SPECIAL.

00:57:12.000 --> 00:57:19.000
Boys Choir:
* THROUGH MANY DANGERS,
TOILS AND SNARES *

00:57:19.000 --> 00:57:22.000
* TOILS AND SNARES *

00:57:22.000 --> 00:57:31.000
* I HAVE ALREADY COME... *

00:57:31.000 --> 00:57:33.000
Turnbull:
THEY HAVE TO BE PREPARED

00:57:33.000 --> 00:57:37.000
TO TAKE THEIR RIGHTFUL PLACE
IN THE SOCIETY.

00:57:37.000 --> 00:57:39.000
IT'S A COMBINATION
OF BEING IN TOUCH

00:57:40.000 --> 00:57:42.000
WITH THEMSELVES SPIRITUALLY

00:57:42.000 --> 00:57:44.000
AND IN TERMS OF FEELING
WHO THEY ARE

00:57:44.000 --> 00:57:47.000
AND MUSIC CAN HELP US
TO DO THAT.

00:57:47.000 --> 00:57:53.000
* ...WILL LEAD ME HOME. *

00:58:11.000 --> 00:58:14.000
YOU'LL HAVE A SERIOUS
COLLECTION, JOSE.

00:58:14.000 --> 00:58:15.000
MY MOTHER SAYS

00:58:15.000 --> 00:58:17.000
SHE WANTS
TO SEE JAPAN...

