00:58:33.000 --> 00:58:36.000
WHY YOU LOOKING THAT WAY?

00:58:36.000 --> 00:58:37.000
FOCUS THAT WAY!

00:58:37.000 --> 00:58:39.000
Turnbull:
IN OTHER COUNTRIES

00:58:39.000 --> 00:58:43.000
THEY USUALLY DO NOT UNDERSTAND
THE ORIGINS OF THE SONG

00:58:43.000 --> 00:58:45.000
BUT IT HAS SUCH
A UNIVERSAL FLAVOR

00:58:45.000 --> 00:58:48.000
AND JUST THE MELODY ITSELF
IS SO BEAUTIFUL.

00:58:48.000 --> 00:58:51.000
THAT'S WHAT REALLY
CAPTURES PEOPLE.

00:58:51.000 --> 00:58:53.000
GOT IT, GUYS?

00:58:53.000 --> 00:58:56.000
Man:
GO DIRECTLY TO
THE DRESSING ROOM.

00:58:56.000 --> 00:58:58.000
DO NOT STOP,
DO NOT PASS GO--

00:58:58.000 --> 00:59:00.000
DIRECTLY TO
THE DRESSING ROOM.

00:59:00.000 --> 00:59:02.000
PUT ON YOUR
BURGUNDY AND BLACK.

00:59:02.000 --> 00:59:06.000
MEET UPSTAIRS BY 2:20.

00:59:06.000 --> 00:59:09.000
NOT 2:25-- 2:20.

00:59:09.000 --> 00:59:10.000
GOT IT?

00:59:10.000 --> 00:59:13.000
Man:
THE ONLY STOP
THAT MAKES SENSE

00:59:13.000 --> 00:59:15.000
IS TO STOP AND
GET YOUR BLAZER.

00:59:16.000 --> 00:59:20.000
Turnbull:
THERE'S A DICHOTOMY
BETWEEN A BUNCH OF BLACK KIDS

00:59:20.000 --> 00:59:21.000
SINGING "AMAZING GRACE"

00:59:21.000 --> 00:59:25.000
OR LET'S SAY A BLACK CHURCH
SINGING "AMAZING GRACE"

00:59:25.000 --> 00:59:28.000
GIVEN THE FACT
THAT THE PERSON WHO WROTE IT

00:59:28.000 --> 00:59:32.000
WAS A HANDLER OF SLAVES,
AND WAS A CAPTAIN OF A SHIP

00:59:32.000 --> 00:59:34.000
THAT CARRIED SLAVES
BACK AND FORTH.

00:59:34.000 --> 00:59:37.000
BUT IT HAS SOME VERY DEEP
AND IMPORTANT WORDS

00:59:38.000 --> 00:59:40.000
AND IMPORTANT MEANING
TO THOSE WORDS

00:59:40.000 --> 00:59:43.000
THAT WE CAN ALL RELATE TO.

00:59:43.000 --> 00:59:47.000
THOSE ARE THE KINDS OF THINGS
THAT MAKE IT UNIVERSAL

00:59:47.000 --> 00:59:49.000
AS OPPOSED TO WHO
IT WAS WRITTEN BY.

00:59:55.000 --> 00:59:58.000
DO YOU THINK GRACE IS REAL
TO THESE KIDS?--

00:59:59.000 --> 01:00:00.000
THIS TRANSFORMING
POWER THAT CAN

01:00:01.000 --> 01:00:02.000
CHANGE A LIFE.

01:00:02.000 --> 01:00:07.000
I DON'T THINK THAT MOST KIDS
RECOGNIZE THAT YET.

01:00:08.000 --> 01:00:13.000
BUT AT THE APPROPRIATE TIME,
THEY WILL REMEMBER.

01:00:14.000 --> 01:00:21.000
* AMAZING GRACE... *

01:00:21.000 --> 01:00:24.000
Boy:
IT FEELS LIKE WALKING
ON A BEACH

01:00:24.000 --> 01:00:27.000
AND LIKE WIND IS HITTING ME
AND STUFF LIKE THAT--

01:00:27.000 --> 01:00:29.000
THAT'S HOW I FEEL ABOUT IT.

01:00:29.000 --> 01:00:32.000
NOT LIKE A ROUGH WIND,
LIKE A SOFT WIND

01:00:32.000 --> 01:00:34.000
JUST COMING BY LIKE A BREEZE--

01:00:34.000 --> 01:00:37.000
THAT'S WHAT I THINK
GRACE MEANS TO ME.

