BUT NOW I SEE. *

01:10:07.000 --> 01:10:09.000
Ritchie:
WHEN I ASKED MY MOTHER

01:10:09.000 --> 01:10:13.000
WHY THESE OLD SONGS WERE SO
SAD AND MOURNFUL SOUNDING--

01:10:13.000 --> 01:10:16.000
THIS WAS WHEN I WAS
A LITTLE GIRL--

01:10:16.000 --> 01:10:20.000
SHE SAID, "WELL, HONEY, THEY'RE
NOT SAD, THEY'RE REVERENT."

01:10:20.000 --> 01:10:24.000
SHE SAID, "YOU GET SO MUCH
MORE JOY OUT OF A SONG

01:10:24.000 --> 01:10:27.000
WHEN YOU RELISH THE NOTES
AND SAVOR THE TUNE."

01:10:31.000 --> 01:10:32.000
Moyers:
WHAT IS IT

01:10:32.000 --> 01:10:35.000
THAT HOLDS A FAMILY
LIKE THIS TOGETHER?

01:10:35.000 --> 01:10:39.000
WELL, THAT'S HARD TO SAY.

01:10:39.000 --> 01:10:43.000
IT'S MEMORIES, I THINK,
IT'S SHARED MEMORIES

01:10:43.000 --> 01:10:46.000
SHARED REALITY, SHARED VALUES.

01:10:46.000 --> 01:10:50.000
AND FOR US, IT'S THE SHARED
SONGS AND THE MUSIC

01:10:50.000 --> 01:10:54.000
THAT REALLY DO STRIKE THOSE
CHORDS INSIDE OF EACH OF US.

